# Chapter Page Layout: No `zoom` Scaling

## Problem with `zoom`

Using CSS `zoom` to shrink a large Figma artboard into smaller viewports creates a **size mismatch** between sections:

- Section with `zoom: 0.8` → 34px title renders visually as 27px
- Adjacent section without zoom → 34px title renders at 34px
- Result: the zoomed section appears smaller than Figma and inconsistent with the rest of the page

## Correct Approach: Proportional CSS

The Figma artboard is **1824px wide**. Map fixed pixel values to proportional equivalents:

| Figma value | CSS equivalent | Formula |
|-------------|---------------|---------|
| `px-[200px]` (section padding) | `px-[11%]` or `paddingInline: 'clamp(24px, 11%, 200px)'` | 200/1824 ≈ 11% |
| `w-[1424px]` (max content width) | `max-w-[1424px] mx-auto w-full` | cap on wide screens |

## Content Area Context

`<main>` has `md:pr-20` = **80px right sidebar**. So within `<main>`, `w-full` = viewport − 80px. Percentage padding is relative to that content width, not the full viewport.

## Desktop Wrapper Template

```jsx
{/* ✅ No zoom — responsive desktop layout */}
<div className="hidden md:block w-full">
  <div className="relative w-full">
    {/* Hero, feature cards, etc. */}

    {/* Section with proportional horizontal padding */}
    <section className="... px-[11%]">
      {/* Cap content on very wide screens */}
      <div className="w-full max-w-[1424px] mx-auto">
        {/* content */}
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
```

## What to Remove if Zoom Exists

- All `CH4_DESKTOP_*` constants and the `getChapter4DesktopScale` function
- `desktopScale` state + `useEffect` resize listener
- `style={{ zoom: ..., width: 'calc(100% + Xpx)' }}` wrapper div
- `overflow-x-hidden` on the outer wrapper (no longer needed)
